        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 6:57PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sherman, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hotchkissville, Haight Vineyard, Pequabuck, Baker Corner, Reynolds
Bridge, Candlewood Trails, Pomeraug, Lower Merryall, Marble Dale,
Harwinton, East Litchfield, Plymouth Green, Morris, Upper Merryall,
Delano Field, Erickson Corner, Dempsey Landing, Bethlehem Village,
Candlewood Point, and Litchfield Green.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
